davide@cad.gatech.edu (davide) writes:
>   My question is, are you only weakining if the person trying to 
>   break the system KNOWS you limited your key choise ?

No, the system is weak whether or not you tell the cryptanalyst about
your mistake.  They will always try to save themselves some work by
guessing you did something dumb.

Is your house only insecure if people KNOW you left it unlocked?  Only
if you also assume that people won't try the knob.



